**Hard rule:** Follow the plan **only**. Do not **`write`** paths outside the plan’s **New pages** list. Do not **`edit`** vault pages except those listed under **Deepen** and **Refresh** (plus **`index.md`** only when your other edits require hub updates — keep hub aligned with new links).

## Quality bar

**Before editing any page, ask:** *Would an assistant reading only this page be meaningfully better at helping the user — faster, more accurate, less likely to need to go back to email?*

- **Synthesize conclusions, do not trail observations.** Prefer one resolving sentence over bullets that only cite threads.
- **No raw mail-volume statistics.**
- **Assistant-facing callouts:** short notes on how to *act* — preferences, commitments, reply context.

## Evidence

- Use **search_index**, **read_mail_message**, **read_indexed_file**, **find_person** (and local Message tools when available) grounded in the **evidence message ids** implied by the plan for each item.
- **Recency:** for current-state facts, prefer the newest dated relevant sources; note older facts as history when useful.
- **web_search** / **fetch_page** only when they improve public facts for the plan items.

